title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\DataTransfer\V1\ImportedDataInfo
name: ImportedDataInfo
description:
Describes data which should be imported.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.datatransfer.v1.ImportedDataInfo

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.sql
params.description: SQL query to run. When empty, API checks that there is only one table_def specified and loads this table. Only Standard SQL queries are accepted. Legacy SQL is not allowed.

params.name: data.destination_table_description
params.description: The description of a destination table. This can be several sentences or paragraphs describing the table contents in detail.

params.name: data.table_defs
params.description: When used WITHOUT the "sql" parameter, describes the schema of the destination table. When used WITH the "sql" parameter, describes tables with data stored outside of BigQuery.

params.name: data.user_defined_functions
params.description: Inline code for User-defined function resources. Ignored when "sql" parameter is empty.

params.name: data.write_disposition
params.description: Specifies the action if the destination table already exists.
